<subSubSection id="C370650EFFC8FFDEFF29F923BB05C80A" pageId="27" pageNumber="248" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD53685FFC8FFDEFF29F923BB05C80A" blockId="27.[136,1452,1742,2093]" pageId="27" pageNumber="248">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC8FFDEFF29F923BE30C9EE" bold="true" box="[136,261,1742,1768]" pageId="27" pageNumber="248">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
—This species is morphologically similar and phylogenetically close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFC8FFDEFBF2F922BBDDC9EE" box="[1107,1256,1743,1768]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="27" pageNumber="248" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="moiwensis">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC8FFDEFBF2F922BBDDC9EE" box="[1107,1256,1743,1768]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="248">P. moiwensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but has distinct lineage, and also has a more round-shape of urediniospores and smaller teliospores.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
